ABAKALIKI – A frontline People’s Democratic Party(PDP) 2023 Presidential Aspirant and former Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF) Senator Anyim Pius Anyim, said that by next month, more lawmakers of the All Progressives Congress would defect to the People’s Democratic Party. Anyim who stated this with optimism, while addressing members of the party during an enlarged meeting of the party in Abakaliki, the State capital on Tuesday, further stated that PDP would soon take over the leadership of the House of Assembly.. He accused 15 Lawmakers of the Assembly who are members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) of desperation and concocting signatures of members in a bid to maintain control of the House. 2023: I Will Run For Governorship In Niger – Malagi Wike Gets Fresh Appointment From PDP, APC Kicks He boasted that without the 9 lawmakers of PDP, the House won’t be able to get 2/3rd majority to do anything. Anyim, a former President of the Senate, accused the fifteen APC lawmakers of trying to control everything that happen in the House. He further urged PDP members to remain committed to the sole agenda of the party, which is, returning to Ebonyi State seat of power come 2023. The 15 APC Lawmakers had on Monday this week, elected the member representing Afikpo North West constituency and Deputy Leader of the House as the Assembly Deputy Speaker after a letter allegedly written by the Deputy Speaker, Hon Obasi Odefa notifying the House of his resignation as a member of the House was read on the floor of the House by the Speaker, Chief Francis Nwifuru. Mr Nwifuru after reading the alleged resignation letter from Mr Obasi declared his seat vacant. POLL But Odefa who is a PDP lawmaker, representing Onicha East State constituency, denied ever writing any resignation letter.